FBIS4-19274 "drweu073_p_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 GREECE Spokesman Calls Letter `Positive' Spokesman Calls Letter `Positive' NC1404183394 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1700 GMT 14 Apr 94 NC1404183394 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today described Albanian President Sali Berisha's letter to the EU [European Union] commission as positive. At the same time, Venizelos stressed that even with a few days' delay, the Albanian side's reaction to Greece's proposals to defuse the situation make things easier. Venizelos said that in the past few days, the Albanian side attempted a dangerous spread of the tension, but Greece's stance was calm and firm from the beginning.
